title: Grateful Dead Live at Capital Centre on 1988-09-03
lineage: Playback of MCs on recording deck (Marantz PMDxxx) > Sony D6 > Maxell XL90s (1st gen). 1st (gen) > Playback on Marantz PRD505 (azimuth adjusted) > Marantz Intergrated Stereo Amp MP-68 > SB Audigy4 on new P4 machine > Sound Forge normalization > WAV > CDWave > WAVs > Flacfrontend 1.7.1 (level 8) > flacs.
description:
Set 1

Let The Good Times Roll 
Feel Like A Stranger ->
Franklin's Tower ->
Little Red Rooster ->
Peggy-O 
Me And My Uncle ->
Big River 
Bird Song 

Set 2

Box Of Rain 
Victim Or The Crime ->
Foolish Heart ->
Man Smart, Woman Smarter ->
Eyes Of The World ->
Drums ->
Space ->
Goin' Down The Road Feeling Bad ->
I Need A Miracle ->
Morning Dew 

Encore
One More Saturday Night 
Ripple

reviews.review_text: I peed my pants .... first electric Ripple in how many years? I peed my fucking pants, I did.

IT HAS BEEN AWHILE IT WAS ONE OF THOSE SHOWS WHERE THE BAND COMES OUT AND DOES NOT LET YOU DOWN BECAUSE IT WAS A GREAT SHOW FOR "88 STANDARDS,AND LOW AND BEHOLD THEY COME OUT WITH SATURDAY NITE SO WE FIGURE INSTEAD OF HEARING THIS FOR LIKE THE 200TH TIME(NO EXAGGERATION)WE WOULD SPLIT AND GET BACK TO THE HOTEL,FOR SOME UNKNOWN REASON MY FRIEND SAYS "YO LETS WAIT AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS" AND JUST ABOUT THE FURTHEST THING IN YOUR MIND IS WOW MAYBE 2NITE "RIPPLE" WILL RE-APPEAR AND SURE ENOUGH IT DOES.JERRY DOES NOT MISS A NOTE OR A VERSE.THE WHOLE REST OF THAT TOUR EVERY NIGHT MOST PEOPLE STAYED UNTIL THE LAST NOTE,BUT IT WAS NOT TO BE.

please dont cirrculate sources like this This is one of the poorest sources on the entire archive.

.....

listen to this one

http://www.archive.org/details/gd1988-09-03.nak100.mchugh.82967.sbeok.flac16

or the sbd

One of 'those nights' A night where the band comes to dance across your heart... I highly doubt there could be truly an unlistenable source for ANY show, let alone THIS one - because with a higher heart you are there and the oneness of all joy parades mellifluously onward into the days arising :)
